.TH listFiles 8 "13 Feb 2017" "version 1.0"
.SH NAME
listFiles \- List files and perform incremental backup
.SH SYNOPSIS
listFiles <source_dir> <dest_dir>
.SH DESCRIPTION
listFiles displays the contents of a directory (source_dir) and then performs backup to a destination directory (dest_dir). Files are only backedup only if the file in the source directory is newer than the file in the destination directory.
.SH OPTIONS
listFiles takes a source directory and then a destination directory as parameters.
.SH EXAMPLE
Example: listFiles /home /backup  